article.headline: Ohio 81, San Francisco 66
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio (AP) -- Sonny Troutman scored 15 points and Mychal Green added 14 to lead Ohio past San Francisco 81-66 Monday night. Green scored 10 of his 14 points in the first half when the Bobcats (1-0) used a 22-8 run to open up a 16-point halftime lead. The Dons (2-1) cut the lead to eight when John Cox hit a jumper with 13:47 left in the game, but Ohio responded with an 8-0 run to push the lead back to 16. Ohio made 13-of-27 shots, 48 percent, in the first half to 35 percent, 8 of 23, for San Francisco. Ohio outscored San Francisco 27 to 12 from the foul line for the game. Jeff Halbert and Leon Williams scored 11 points apiece for Ohio. Terren Harbut had 10 points and eight rebounds. Cox led San Francisco with 26 points, but made just 8 of 23 shots from the field. Jerome Gumbs had 11 points and Tyrone Riley pulled down 10 rebounds.
